parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: (a) I am awake (in the night), watch, (b) I am watchful, on the alert, vigilant. From egeiro; to keep awake, i.e. Watch.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: From a presumed derivative of histemi; to set fast, i.e. to turn resolutely in a certain direction, or to confirm.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Left, left behind, the remainder, the rest, the others. Masculine plural of a derivative of leipo; remaining ones.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Nominative Neuter Plural
Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: A strengthened form of melo; to intend, i.e. Be about to be, do, or suffer something.
To be dying, be about to die, wither, decay. From apo and thnesko; to die off.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Singular
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
From a primary ergo; toil; by implication, an act.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Middle or Passive - Accusative Neuter Plural
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.
Neuter of a compound of en and a derivative of optanomai; in the face of.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
